<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="1537" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="24.[178,1085,959,1010]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1537">Diagnosis: There are 17 spines on the anterior margin of the protibia; among congeners, only in specimens of this species are there more than ten.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="1537" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[178,1086,1025,1282]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1537">
Description: Size: Length 15.0 mm; width 8.0 mm. Form: As in 
<figureCitation box="[922,1007,1025,1048]" captionStart="Figs 153-156" captionStartId="50.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-60@50.[178,1085,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="Figs 153-156: Habitus illustrations of (153) Aspitonis undulicornis, holotype; (154) Isoforma biguttula, holotype; (155) I. fritilla, holotype; (156) I. goryi, non-type." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5294886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5294886/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="1537">Fig. 156</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium mostly black, with flavotestaceous line behind eyes; pronotum mostly black, upper sides flavotestaceous; elytral disc mostly black, with midelytral flavotestaceous fascia, the humeral angle may be flavotestaceous. Head: Antennal capitulum very long (
<figureCitation box="[186,262,1143,1165]" captionStart="Figs 70-80" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1351,1373]" captionTargetBox="[178,1100,235,1309]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1100,212,1333]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 70-80: Antennae. (70) Isoforma fritilla, female; (71) I. goryi, female; (72) Isoforma planata, female; (73) Pilosirus brunoi, male; (74) Isoforma subgilva, female; (75) Pilosirus amazonicus, female; (76) P. fasciatus, female; (77) Platynoptera carti, male; (78) P. flavohumeralis, male; (79) P. humeralis, male; (80) P. lyciformis, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5294864" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5294864/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="1537">Fig. 71</figureCitation>
), each capitular antennomere as long as funicle; antennal carina very prominent; EW/FW 22/35. Thorax: Pronotal anterior margin linear, not projected at middle; side margins of disc rounded at middle; PW/PL 100/80; elytra conspicuously flared; disc with 4 discal carinae; EL/EW 200/140. Abdomen: Female pygidium not incised at distal margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[178,864,1297,1319]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1537" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="24.[178,864,1297,1319]" box="[178,864,1297,1319]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1537">Natural history: One specimen was collected in August.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="1537" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[178,1085,1334,1386]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1537">Variation: Size: length 10.0-15.0 mm; width 4.0-8.0 mm. The flavotestaceous macula on the humeral angle varies in expression.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
